    70Ôćĺmacro_rules! __ensure {
   174Ôćĺ/// Construct an ad-hoc error from a string or existing non-`anyhow` error
   175Ôćĺ/// value.
   176Ôćĺ///
   177Ôćĺ/// This evaluates to an [`Error`][crate::Error]. It can take either just a
   178Ôćĺ/// string, or a format string with arguments. It also can take any custom type
   179Ôćĺ/// which implements `Debug` and `Display`.
   180Ôćĺ///
   181Ôćĺ/// If called with a single argument whose type implements `std::error::Error`
   182Ôćĺ/// (in addition to `Debug` and `Display`, which are always required), then that
